      <tr class='proposal_row' id='proposal_row_58'>
        <td rowspan='2' class='description'>
          <h3>
            <a href="../../../login" class="favorite favorite_58"><span>*</span></a>
            
              <a href="../../../proposals/58" class="title">SELinux policy within package managers, why policy is special</a>
            
            
          </h3>

          <div class="excerpt">
            SELinux policy is currently installed from a single or multiple package(s) as an application which breaks the linkage between policy and the software they are constraining. We will talk about a way to treat policy specially without adding downfalls such as a large increase in packages.
          </div>
        </td>

        
        <td class='track block track-2'>
          <a href="../../2009/tracks/2">Security</a>
        </td>
        

        
